feedbacks.review_text: I got my horizontally impacted wisdom tooth extracted by Dr. T. Ramakrishna @Dental Profiles Clinic, JP Nagar 7th phase. I don't recommend this Doctor and clinic

Although I went there with positive mindset by reading the feedback here, I felt nothing is organized and the concern or care shown was little more and dramatic, not really genuine. I was suggested to get all 4 teeth removed same day and when I go inside for the procedure doctor himself was shocked that x-ray was not taken earlier!! that made me little nervous. and the receptionist does multitasking including taking x-rays, arrange tools and adjust light and suction, etc without using gloves!! I didn't find that really professional at least for the money they charged for very straightforward            I had braces in place. No precaution was taken to avoid damage to either braces or gums. As everyone says doctor did his job very confidently and without pain on the spot,                         I thought he would stop but he encouraged me to finish all same day.  For me he didn't explain any procedure or precaution before surgery despite asking. when asked about precaution or post surgery care, receptionist said she will give post surgery. When I asked before should I refrain from brushing, doctor said no need. but after surgery he only suggested not to brush for 2 days!! I got a shock as to why I trusted!! but then as he told earlier with 6 six injections I had painless procedure but had pain for a week which would reduce only with pain killers. Ulcer from the bruise an added and most troublesome pain where I could not talk or eat or smile. When I visited my orthodontist,                                              I had to visit twice    and guess what The main doctor is not seen after surgery although they always say the main doctor is there!! Why lie?                             During suture removal, the assistant doctor adjusted light with gloved fingers and uses same to remove suture.  I had asked specifically if i had to get someone, but doctor said no need. But I realized such a big mistake I did by accepting that.                                             But be assured, as everyone says won't have pain as you will be given enough injections. Maybe I expected too much from earlier feedback I guess, hence little taken aback.
